GABARONE - Former Botswana President Ketumile Masire will be laid to rest on Thursday.Masire died last week at the age of 91 at a Gabarone hospital.The former head of state will be buried in his home village next to his late wife.READ: Former Botswana president dies at 91His body lay in state at the country's Parliament where it was viewed by the public.Masire is praised for promoting the social and economic well-being of Botswana during his 18-year reign.He's also credited for bringing stability to that country.Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe and former president Thabo Mbeki are among the dignitaries expected.eNCA